title: Distribution element schema
description: Distribution element schema generated by the CEDAR Template Editor 2.5.38

propertyDescriptions.distributionIdentifier: A globally unique string that identifies the dataset distribution.
propertyDescriptions.distributionIdentifierType: The identifier type used to identify the dataset distribution.
propertyDescriptions.distributionDate: Date when the dataset was distributed.
propertyDescriptions.distributionFormat: An established standard to which the dataset distribution conforms to.
propertyDescriptions.distributionMediaType: A media type, formerly known as a MIME type, of dataset distribution.
propertyDescriptions.Distributor: Information about the distributor of this dataset distribution. The Distributor includes primarily the system doing the distribution, but can include the person or persons responsible as well, for example the person who reformatted the dataset for this distribution.

propertyDescriptions.distributorRole: The role of the distributor in bringing the described dataset into existence.

propertyDescriptions.distributorEmail1: An email address of the distributor.

propertyDescriptions.distributorName: The full name of the distributor.
propertyDescriptions.distributorGivenName: If the distributor is a person, the personal name(s) of the distributor (e.g., first and optionally middle name in Western languagues, optionally middle and last name in Asian languages).
propertyDescriptions.distributorFamilyName: If the distributor is a person, the surname(s) of the distributor (e.g., last name in Western languagues, first name in Asian languages).
